Cosmon — open-core license map
===============================

Cosmon ships under an open-core split (operator decision 2026-06-21,
delib-20260620-ca76; doctrine in docs/adr/092-license-bascule-mpl-to-agpl.md):

  • The kernel, persistence/ports, product CLI & runtime, agent engine,
    cockpit/UX, and the multi-tenant federation SERVER are licensed under
    the GNU Affero General Public License, version 3 only (AGPL-3.0-only).
    Full text: ./LICENSE-AGPL  —  https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

  • The pure network SDK that third parties link to *talk to* a cosmon
    instance over the wire (cosmon-thin-cli, cosmon-thin-macro,
    cosmon-client) — and the vendored third-party / sibling-galaxy crates —
    are licensed under the Apache License, version 2.0 (Apache-2.0).
    Full text: ./LICENSE-APACHE  —  http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

The governing rule — the "network-boundary doctrine" — is:

    A crate may stay Apache-2.0 IFF its real `[dependencies]` closure
    contains zero AGPL crates, i.e. it reaches the AGPL core only over the
    network (HTTP/IPC), never by code-linking. Any Apache crate that
    code-links an AGPL crate is a license contradiction and must flip to
    AGPL.

Each crate declares its own `license` in its Cargo.toml (SPDX expression),
and every first-party `.rs` source file carries a matching
`// SPDX-License-Identifier:` header. The authoritative per-crate
partition and the rationale live in:

  • docs/adr/092-license-bascule-mpl-to-agpl.md  (doctrine)
  • NOTICE                                        (vendored attributions)
  • deny.toml + .github/workflows/deny.yml        (CI license gate)

Vendored third-party and sibling-galaxy code retains its upstream license;
see NOTICE for the enumeration.

